  "messages": [
    {
      "id": "7228618f435112bcf053030189e1899adf7734ed",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-14 11:17:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\ni'm totally against the patch. umask makes zero sense below MDD. i'm not sure, but at the moment i tend to think it doesn't makes sense on the server as well.\nthis approach was introduced with LU-974 and I think that was mistake too.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "4bbd4fe20480c76869ad7664fc9da9acb2e80f21",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-14 18:55:01.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAlex, my understanding (which is unfortunately incomplete) is that the umask needs to be handled at the MDS side, since it affects the ACL behaviour, and cannot be \"flattened\" into the ACL since can be set on a per-process basis.  It also cannot be done only on the client, since the file creation mode may depend on the parent directory default ACL (?) and permission checks are typically handled on the server.\n\nThat said, I agree that it shouldn't be needed inside the OSD/OUT/OSP.  My understanding is that all of the mode/permission checks should be handled at the MDT/MDD level before anything gets to the OSD.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "2af4f0a29180b905f004e715f4113b17e59d1d1a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-14 19:01:36.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nyes.. if we can't handle this on the client, then MDD is the place to do. immediate result of the original fix is that we do fail few tests (including sanity/103) with zfs.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "e42f88cef37e5fd36b8ad4ee2f50fb5df8f66479",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-14 19:03:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nactually I asked for the details in LU-974, hope to understand this better a bit.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
