      "date": "2013-03-06 00:48:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nHmm, it seems the failure is not caused by this bug. in test script we use ls -s here, but in zfs, ls -s seems always get 1 for a new touched file.\r\n\r\n[3/5/13 4:46:01 PM] wangdi: I got this on lustre + zfs\r\n[3/5/13 4:46:04 PM] wangdi: [root@testnode tests]# ls -s /mnt/lustre/a\r\n1 /mnt/lustre/a\r\n[root@testnode tests]# ll /mnt/lustre/\r\ntotal 1\r\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 0 Dec 20 11:31 a\r\n[3/5/13 4:46:33 PM] wangdi: ls -s and ll get different file size, is this know or a bug?\r\n[3/5/13 4:47:01 PM] wangdi: though on ldiskfs, ll and ls -s get the same size.\r\n\r\nnew ticket?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
